> Argentina is very much a culture that focuses on togetherness. This dinner idea takes a little time and care, but it's worth it! Bavette steak is pounded thin, breaded in a light-as-air coating, and fried to crispy golden-brown perfection. Add a fried egg on top (a caballo) drizzled with a spicy parsley-garlic chimichurri, crispy potato wedges with a tangy green salad, for bright crunchy contrast.

== Roasted Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until
browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Chimichurri ==

While potatoes roast, peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Roughly chop
@parsley{¼%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine garlic, parsley, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, half the
@red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt{pinch},
@pepper{}, and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Refrigerate chimichurri
until ready to serve.

== Salad ==

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}, separate leaves and chop into
bite-size pieces. Cut @tomato{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, whisk together remaining vinegar, @olive oil{1%tablespoon},
@sugar{¼%teaspoon}, a pinch of salt, and pepper. Add lettuce and tomato; toss to coat.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

== Milanesa ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces
of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until steak is about ½ inch
thick. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place @flour{1%tablespoon} in a #shallow dish{}. In a separate shallow dish, whisk
half the @eggs{4} with @water{1%tablespoon}. Place @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup} in a
third shallow dish and season with salt and pepper.

Working one piece at a time, press steak into flour until fully coated. Gently shake
off excess, then dip both sides into beaten egg. Let excess egg drip off, then press
into seasoned panko until fully coated.

Heat a 1⁄3-inch layer of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large, #heavy-bottomed pan{}
over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added
to the pan, add steak and cook until crust is golden brown and steak is cooked to
desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, work in batches, adding
more oil as needed.)

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{} and sprinkle with a pinch
of salt. Tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Wash out pan.

== Fried Eggs ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Once hot, crack
remaining eggs into pan. Fry eggs to preference. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide potatoes, salad, and steak between plates. Top steak with fried eggs and drizzle
with chimichurri. Serve.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.